{
  "texts": [
    "The evaluation metric used was the Pearson correlation coefficient between the predicted and actual similarity scores, where a higher indicates a stronger linear relationship between predictions and ground truth scores.",
    "Submissions were assessed based on the Pearson correlation coefficient calculated as:𝑟 = ∑ (𝑥 𝑖 -𝑥 ̅)(𝑦 𝑖 -𝑦 ̅) 𝑁 √ ∑ (𝑥 𝑖 -𝑥 ̅) 2 𝑁 √ ∑ (𝑦 𝑖 -𝑦 ̅) 2 𝑁(3)where 𝑥 𝑖 and 𝑦 𝑖 represent individual data points, 𝑥̅ and 𝑦 ̅ are the means of 𝑥 and 𝑦, respectively, and 𝑁 is the number of data set samples.",
    "The Pearson correlation coefficient measures the strength of the linear relationship between predicted and actual similarity scores, reflecting model performance in patent phrase similarity.",
    "We rigorously evaluated our model's performance and generalization with a 4-fold Cross-Validation [18] approach.",
    "E. ResultsIn this section, we present the performance evaluation of our model variants (denoted as V1, V2, and V3) using the DeBERTa-v3-large architecture."
  ]
}